The appointment of Major General Farouk Yahaya as the new Chief of Army Staff has been confirmed by the Nigerian Senate on Tuesday, June 22.  The red chamber took the decision following the consideration of the report of its joint committee on Defence and Army led by senators Aliyu Wamakko and Ali Ndume. The President of the Senate had on June 2, referred the request of the President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), for Yahaya’s confirmation to the committees. The Defence Committee which is chaired by Wamakko was mandated to be the lead panel to screen the newly appointed Army Chief.   Source By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Senate on Wednesday received an executive bill seeking to increase the retirement age for teachers in the country from 60 to 65 years.  The bill also seeks to extend the years of service for teachers from 35 to 40 years.  President Muhammadu… In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja - President Muhamadu Buhari has appointed Major General Farouk Yahaya new chief of army staff. A statement by the acting director defence information, Brigadier general Onyema Nwachukwu made this known. Before this appointment, Yahaya was the General officer commanding Division 1 of the Nigerian Army. He… In "Top Stories" The new service chiefs appointed by President Muhammadu Buhari have been confirmed by the senate. The Senate confirmed the new service chiefs on Tuesday after the consideration of the report of the Committee on Defence which recommended their confirmation. The Senate President, Ahmad Lawan, had on Wednesday, penultimate week, referred… In "News"